From:MCsweet
MEOH,

Sold some today on bad news about Peru cutting 30% of the supply to one of
their plants. I still like the stock, but think it could trade down on the
news, giving a short-term buying opportunity.

We will see. News follows (not on Yahoo yet)

MC

Chile, Jun 17, 2004 (BNamericas.com via COMTEX) -- Vancouver-based methanol
producer Methanex Corporation has reduced methanol production by 30% at its
Cabo Negro facility in Chile's southern Region XII due to gas supply cuts from
Argentina, newspaper Estrategia quoted Methanex's Latin America VP Rodolfo
Krause as saying.

The company has seen its gas supplies cut by 1.7 million cubic meters a day
(mcm/d), which is 30% of its total requirement.

"We don't have the possibility of using an alternative fuel so natural gas is a
non-substitutable supply for us, and if the restrictions are 30%, this means
our production decreases by that much," Krause said.

However, Krause is optimistic of a resolution to the crisis in the short-term.

"We expect that in [southern hemisphere] spring-summer the situation will
normalize completely. I would like to be more optimistic and think this will
happen in August but I don't have a crystal ball," he said.

The Cabo Negro facility, which started operations in 1988, is Methanex's
largest and lowest cost facility.

It employs 450 people and its three trains have a combined annual capacity of
three million tons (mt), which will rise to nearly 4mt when a new production
plant, currently under construction, is commissioned by year-end.

Methanex officials were not immediately available for comment.

http://www.bnamericas.com
