Date:6/18/2004 4:33:59 PM
From:Paul Senior
Suma, you might also check major stockholders lists of the banks you are
interested in for investor Jeffrey Gendell of Tontine Partners. He takes large
positions; he can be a long-term investor, but also one who can prod bank
management to realize value for shareholders. He specializes in small, local
banks/thrifts, and has - or so my reading leads me to believe - a good record
here for getting taken out in takeovers. Also, fwiw, in an article in Barron's
he said he was buying small banks in areas where there was coal mining: he
believes coal business will do well, thus putting money in hands of local
miners and local businesses. He figures the local banks consequently will do
well and could be buyout candidates.
