%BOM---------------------
Date:6/25/2004 1:15:57 AM
From:Spekulatius
OVTI - barriers to entry?
I think there are substantial barriers to entry. OVTI's market are image
sensors build using CMOS technology. CMOS is a standard technology used for
many semiconductor products (Memory etc.). Traditionally, image sensors were
build using CCD (charged coupled devices) which is a more expensive andf i
think they also consume more power. For low cost mass market products, CMOS
sensors should be cheaper. My understanding is that OVTI deploys a proprietary
method/design for its sensors which may represent a substantial hurdle for
competitors:
http://www.ovt.com/i_technology.html

I think OVTI is an interesting story in an exlosive market (camera phones, low
end digital cameras etc.0 but obviously not without risk.
