From:Paul Senior
I'm not sure where increased oil from OPEC will be going, but it seems that
demand will continue to be high in the USA. I believe that that means there
will be increased gasoline supplies produced. If so, then ADM, with its ethanol
(additive) production, might see demand sustained or increased too (and maybe
profits).

I also like that ADM's expanding its business line of zero/low trans-fat oils
and margarines. "The increased capacity will help satisfy the food industry's
demands as it moves forward to meet the January 1, 2006, FDA labeling
requirement."

Hard for me to see if there'll be significantly increased profits from these
particular activities - ADM's just such a behemoth with many businesses - but
if the stock market holds up, I'll bet that ADM stock will too.

I'll take some at current price.

